overview: The user requested a thorough browser-based test of the sleep
  questionnaire application. The assistant systematically navigated through the
  application, testing the questionnaire flow, form validation, report
  generation, PDF download, and admin login functionality. Key findings included
  confirmation of correct navigation, dynamic form fields, successful PDF
  generation, robust form validation, and proper admin authentication. Minor
  issues identified were ESLint warnings and an outdated page title. Following
  the testing, the user requested fixes. The assistant updated the page title
  and then created a series of atomic commits to incorporate new features and
  enhancements, such as updated schema fields, new sections for pain and mental
  health, a comprehensive sleep analysis report, an enhanced PDF report, updated
  form mock data, and a detailed CSV export, ensuring all changes were logically
  grouped and committed with conventional commit messages.
